main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were sighted over Palm Springs, California on July 26, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as being oval, silver-white in color, and moving at extremely fast speeds.
The objects were observed from a radar site and their movements were tracked visually.
The objects were reported to have a 'fire wake' or trail behind them as they moved.
The sightings were reported by multiple civilian and military witnesses, including a radar guard named A/C Van Dean.
The weather conditions were clear with good visibility at the time of the sightings.
sighted object: oval, silver-white objects moving at high speeds
witnesses: civilian and military personnel at a radar site
photographs: yes, the report includes photographs of the objects
